Five British jihadis killed by US air strikes may have been trainee al-Qaeda suicide bombers, according to intelligence agencies.

Those killed include 19-year-old Ibrahim Kamara, who quit his studies in Brighton to join militants in Syria.

It’s thought that they were fighting for the al-Qaeda-linked al-Nusra Front.

